# Web UI

## Architecture

- **Frontend:** Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite in `frontend/`
- **API:** `ChatHandler` in `src/als_intel/webui.py`
- **Static serving:** `src/als_intel/static_frontend.py` serves `assets/dist/` (SPA)

## Conventions

- UI components live in `frontend/src/components/`; route shells in `frontend/src/views/`
- API client wrappers in `frontend/src/api/`; shared types in `frontend/src/types/`
- i18n source of truth: `src/als_intel/i18n/locales/*.json` (sync via `frontend/scripts/sync-locales.mjs`)
- API responses use `_json_response`; streaming events use `_stream_json_event`
- Auth/CSRF: follow existing protected POST handler patterns; never skip CSRF on authenticated writes
- Extend `tests/test_webui_api.py` for every new or changed API route
- Build frontend before Docker: `make frontend-build` (or multi-stage Dockerfile)

## Dev workflow

```bash
# Terminal 1
make web-dev        # API on :8000 (.venv Python)

# Terminal 2
make frontend-dev   # Vite on :5173, proxies /api to :8000
```

Open `http://localhost:5173/` in dev (not `/app-assets/`). Production builds use `base: /app-assets/` and are served from `assets/dist/`.

Database explorer (`DbExplorerModal.vue`): fixed-height modal, infinite-scroll list, in-modal node detail with source links, reliability breakdowns, and dotted-underline field helpers (`UiFieldHelp`). Result counts use `formatCompactCount()` from `frontend/src/i18n/numbers.ts`.

DB status popover (`DbStatusPopover.vue`, `ManualSyncSourceRow.vue`): compact locale-aware counts and relative timestamps (`formatRelativeTime`, `formatCompactCount`); sync progress shows percent and contextual title; navbar badge shows a spinning sync icon while updating; cooldown button reads "Already up-to-date". Success/error toasts use `last_completion_status` from `/api/sync/manual/status` (not merely "sync stopped").

Manual sync backend (`manual_sync.py`): writes `manual_sync_events` audit rows; exposes `last_completion_status`, `last_completion_error`, and `audit_events` on status API; plan `max_results: 0` means unbounded fetch (connectors treat <=0 as no limit). Source breakdown returns top 5 sources + Others.

Shared overlay motion lives in `frontend/src/styles/main.css` (`.overlay-fade-*`, `.panel-scale-*`, `.page-fade-*`) and is wired through `UiModal`, `UiDrawer`, and `UiPopover`. `AppShell` delays collapsing the assistant shell until the route leave transition finishes so the evidence column does not flash full-width.

## Assistant view

Two-column layout at `lg+` when evidence panel is open: scrollable chat transcript (center) | `EvidenceSidebar` (right). Chat uses full remaining viewport height: markdown report scrolls above a bottom-docked composer.

**Composer** (`ChatComposer.vue`): ChatGPT-style prompt dock with `+` menu (database explorer, filter modal), `ModelPicker` (Ollama catalog + Auto; selection in `localStorage` key `als_model_selection`), send button inside bottom-right of textarea, single rotating status line below prompt (`useStreamStatus` maps `streamPhase` to `app.stream_*` i18n keys). Model list comes from `GET /api/models`; chat resolves `model: "auto"` via `resolve_chat_model` in `llm.py`.

Chat evidence loading (quality-safe latency): candidates are fetched lean (no `claim_text`) with limit `max(context_limit * 10, 200)` unless `evidence_max_rows` / `ALS_CHAT_EVIDENCE_MAX_ROWS` is a positive override. Contradiction pairing runs on the prioritized prompt-candidate set. Cited claim rows are hydrated by id (including escape-hatch ids outside the candidate window) before verification and the sidebar payload.

**Query / report** (`StreamReport.vue`, `MarkdownContent.vue`): full answer rendered as sanitized markdown HTML during stream and after completion. Session actions appear after first user message or loaded session.

**Evidence sidebar** (`EvidenceSidebar.vue`): collapsible via `UiDisclosure` + `app.evidenceCollapsed` (default open). When collapsed on `lg+`, the third grid column is removed so the query column expands; reopen via the **Evidence Nodes** button in `AssistantView.vue`. Idle hint before first query (`app.evidence_hint_idle`); empty hint when report has zero cited rows (`app.evidence_hint_empty`). Contradiction highlighting/sorting follows `app.filters.highlight_contradictions` in `EvidenceRow.vue` / `EvidenceList.vue`.

Settings (`SettingsDrawer.vue`): editable section (language, temperature/timeout sliders with visible helper text); read-only section (host, context limit from `/api/status` — model choice lives in the composer picker, not Settings). Shared form primitives: `UiInput`, `UiSelect`, `UiSliderField`. `status` store seeds `app.config` once from `/api/status` on first refresh.
